          <div  class="use-float-friendly-lists field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden long-text"><h2>Findings</h2>

<ul>
	<li>Observed recidivism rates of sex offenders are underestimates of actual reoffending.</li>
	<li>Measurement variations across studies (operational definitions, length of the follow-up period, populations being studied, methods used) often produce disparate findings.</li>
	<li>Sexual recidivism rates range from 5 percent after three years to 24 percent after 15 years.</li>
	<li>The rates of recidivism for general crime are higher than those for sex crimes.</li>
	<li>Different types of sex offenders have different rates of recidivism.</li>
</ul></div>

